files.Summary: Add a unique constraint.

files.Title: Migration.BigIntType
files.Summary: 64-bit signed integer: -9.2E18 to 9.2E18.

files.Title: Migration.BinaryType
files.Summary: Fixed-length binary data. Always padded to exact length.

files.Title: Migration.BlobType
files.Summary: Unlimited binary storage. No length parameter needed. Maps to BLOB (SQLite), BYTEA (Postgres), VARBINARY(MAX) (SQL Server).

files.Title: Migration.BoolDefault
files.Summary: A boolean literal value. Maps to true/false on Postgres, 1/0 on SQLite.

files.Title: Migration.BooleanType
files.Summary: Boolean true/false value. No parameters needed.

files.Title: Migration.CharType
files.Summary: Fixed-length ASCII/single-byte character string. Always padded to exact length.

files.Title: Migration.CheckConstraintDefinition
files.Summary: Check constraint that spans multiple columns.

files.Title: Migration.ColumnBuilder
files.Summary: Builder for creating column definitions.

files.Title: Migration.ColumnDefinition
files.Summary: Column definition with type and all database-agnostic constraints.

files.Title: Migration.CreateIndexOperation
files.Summary: Create an index on a table.

files.Title: Migration.CreateTableOperation
files.Summary: Create a new table.

files.Title: Migration.CurrentDateDefault
files.Summary: Current date (no time component). Maps to CURRENT_DATE on both platforms.

files.Title: Migration.CurrentTimeDefault
files.Summary: Current time (no date component). Maps to CURRENT_TIME on both platforms.

files.Title: Migration.CurrentTimestampDefault
files.Summary: Current timestamp (without timezone). Maps to CURRENT_TIMESTAMP on both platforms.

files.Title: Migration.CurrentTimestampTzDefault
files.Summary: Current timestamp with timezone. Maps to CURRENT_TIMESTAMP on Postgres (TIMESTAMPTZ), CURRENT_TIMESTAMP on SQLite (stored as text).

files.Title: Migration.DateTimeOffsetType
files.Summary: Date and time with timezone offset. No precision parameter. Always stores full precision with timezone info.

files.Title: Migration.DateTimeType
files.Summary: Date and time without timezone.

files.Title: Migration.DateType
files.Summary: Date only (no time component). No parameters needed.

files.Title: Migration.DdlGenerator
files.Summary: Static helper for DDL generation delegates. Each database provider implements these as static methods.

files.Title: Migration.DecimalDefault
files.Summary: A decimal/floating point literal value.

files.Title: Migration.DecimalType
files.Summary: Exact decimal number with specified precision and scale. Precision = total number of digits (1-38). Scale = digits after decimal point (0 to Precision). Example: DECIMAL(10,2) stores values like 12345678.99

files.Title: Migration.DoubleType
files.Summary: 64-bit IEEE 754 floating point. ~15 significant digits.

files.Title: Migration.DropColumnOperation
files.Summary: Drop a column. DESTRUCTIVE - requires explicit opt-in.

files.Title: Migration.DropForeignKeyOperation
files.Summary: Drop a foreign key constraint.

files.Title: Migration.DropIndexOperation
files.Summary: Drop an index.

files.Title: Migration.DropTableOperation
files.Summary: Drop a table. DESTRUCTIVE - requires explicit opt-in.

files.Title: Migration.EnumType
files.Summary: Database enumeration type with named values. Postgres: Creates actual ENUM type. SQL Server/SQLite: Maps to constrained string.

files.Title: Migration.FloatType
files.Summary: 32-bit IEEE 754 floating point. ~7 significant digits.

files.Title: Migration.ForeignKeyAction
files.Summary: Foreign key referential action.

files.Title: Migration.ForeignKeyActionYamlConverter
files.Summary: YAML type converter for ForeignKeyAction enum.

files.Title: Migration.ForeignKeyDefinition
files.Summary: Foreign key constraint definition.

files.Title: Migration.GeographyType
files.Summary: Spatial geography type for Earth-surface GIS data.

files.Title: Migration.GeometryType
files.Summary: Spatial geometry type for GIS data.

files.Title: Migration.IndexDefinition
files.Summary: Index definition (unique or non-unique). Supports both column-based indexes (Columns) and expression-based indexes (Expressions). When Expressions is non-empty, it takes precedence over Columns.

files.Title: Migration.IntDefault
files.Summary: An integer literal value.

files.Title: Migration.IntType
files.Summary: 32-bit signed integer: -2,147,483,648 to 2,147,483,647.

files.Title: Migration.JsonType
files.Summary: JSON document storage. No parameters needed. Maps to JSONB (Postgres), TEXT (SQLite), NVARCHAR(MAX) (SQL Server).

files.Title: Migration.LiteralDefault
files.Summary: A literal SQL expression to use as-is (no translation). Use this for platform-specific expressions when needed.

files.Title: Migration.LqlDefaultTranslator
files.Summary: Translates LQL default expressions to platform-specific SQL. Provides consistent behavior across PostgreSQL and SQLite.

files.Title: Migration.MigrationError
files.Summary: Migration error with message and optional inner exception.

files.Title: Migration.MigrationOptions
files.Summary: Options for migration execution.

files.Title: Migration.MigrationRunner
files.Summary: Migration runner for executing schema operations.

files.Title: Migration.MoneyType
files.Summary: Currency type with fixed precision for financial calculations. Equivalent to DECIMAL(19,4) - supports values up to ~922 trillion.

files.Title: Migration.NCharType
files.Summary: Fixed-length Unicode character string. Always padded to exact length. Uses 2 bytes per character (UCS-2/UTF-16).

files.Title: Migration.NVarCharType
files.Summary: Variable-length Unicode character string up to max length. Uses 2 bytes per character (UCS-2/UTF-16).

files.Title: Migration.NewUuidDefault
files.Summary: Generate a new random UUID. Maps to gen_random_uuid() on Postgres, a UUID-generating expression on SQLite.

files.Title: Migration.NextSequenceDefault
files.Summary: Next value from a named sequence. Maps to nextval('sequence_name') on Postgres. SQLite: Not supported, use AUTOINCREMENT instead.

files.Title: Migration.NullDefault
files.Summary: Null as default (for nullable columns). Explicit NULL default.

files.Title: Migration.PortableDefault
files.Summary: Platform-independent default value expression. These get translated to the correct SQL for each database platform.

files.Title: Migration.PortableDefaults
files.Summary: Factory methods for portable defaults.

files.Title: Migration.PortableType

files.Title: Migration.PortableTypeJsonConverter
files.Summary: JSON converter for PortableType discriminated union.

files.Title: Migration.PortableTypeYamlConverter
files.Summary: YAML type converter for PortableType discriminated union. Serializes types as simple strings like "Text", "Int", "VarChar(255)".

files.Title: Migration.PortableTypes
files.Summary: Factory methods for portable types.

files.Summary: Result of a schema migration operation.

files.Summary: PostgreSQL DDL generator for schema operations.

files.Summary: Inspects PostgreSQL database schema and returns a SchemaDefinition.

files.Title: Migration.PrimaryKeyDefinition
files.Summary: Primary key constraint definition.

files.Title: Migration.RowVersionType
files.Summary: Row version / timestamp for optimistic concurrency. Auto-generated binary value that changes on each update. No parameters - platform determines size (8 bytes typically).

files.Title: Migration.SQLite.SqliteDdlGenerator
files.Summary: SQLite DDL generator for schema operations.

files.Title: Migration.SQLite.SqliteSchemaInspector
files.Summary: Inspects SQLite database schema and returns a SchemaDefinition.

files.Title: Migration.Schema
files.Summary: Backward-compatible alias for SchemaFactory.

files.Title: Migration.SchemaBuilder
files.Summary: Builder for creating schema definitions.

files.Title: Migration.SchemaDefinition
files.Summary: Complete database schema definition.

files.Summary: Fluent builder for schema definitions.

files.Summary: Base type for schema migration operations. Pattern match to get specific operation details.

files.Title: Migration.SchemaYamlSerializer
files.Summary: Serializes and deserializes schema definitions to/from YAML. Used for storing schema definitions as portable configuration files.

files.Title: Migration.SmallIntType
files.Summary: 16-bit signed integer: -32,768 to 32,767.

files.Title: Migration.SmallMoneyType
files.Summary: Small currency type with reduced precision. Equivalent to DECIMAL(10,4) - supports values up to ~214,748.

files.Title: Migration.StringDefault
files.Summary: A string literal value, properly quoted.

files.Title: Migration.TableBuilder
files.Summary: Builder for creating table definitions.

files.Title: Migration.TableDefinition
files.Summary: Single table definition with columns, indexes, and all constraints.

files.Title: Migration.TextType
files.Summary: Unlimited length text storage. No length parameter needed. Maps to TEXT (Postgres/SQLite), NVARCHAR(MAX) (SQL Server).

files.Title: Migration.TimeType
files.Summary: Time only (no date component) with fractional seconds precision.

files.Title: Migration.TinyIntType
files.Summary: 8-bit integer: 0 to 255 (unsigned) or -128 to 127 (signed).

files.Title: Migration.UniqueConstraintDefinition
files.Summary: Unique constraint (alternative to unique index for semantic clarity).

files.Title: Migration.UuidType
files.Summary: 128-bit globally unique identifier. No parameters needed.

files.Title: Migration.VarBinaryType
files.Summary: Variable-length binary data up to max length.

files.Title: Migration.VarCharType
files.Summary: Variable-length ASCII/single-byte character string up to max length.

files.Title: Migration.XmlType
files.Summary: XML document storage. No parameters needed. Maps to XML (SQL Server/Postgres), TEXT (SQLite).
